  "blurb": "A five-bedroom villa perched in the Bophut hills, its main pavilion opening straight onto a rim-flow pool that seems to spill toward the bay below. Timber-framed entrances, stone-clad walls and a private gym sit within mature flowering gardens, a short drive above Bophut’s beaches and Fisherman’s Village.",
  "detail": "Set on the green slopes above Bophut, this villa is arranged to make the most of a long outlook across the north coast toward the neighbouring islands. The upper living pavilion opens through full-width glass to a terrace and infinity-edge pool, where the water line meets the treetops and the bay beyond — a view that shifts from bright blue days to the scattered lights of the coast at dusk.\n\nInside, the mood is calm and tactile: pale stone floors, a stacked-stone feature wall and a pivoting hardwood door that leads up shallow steps into the open-plan living and dining area. Five en-suite bedrooms are spread across the levels, several with their own balconies angled toward the sea, while a private gym adds a practical touch for longer stays.\n\nThe grounds are a real feature in their own right — a sweep of lawn edged with frangipani and flowering shrubs, framed by tall palms and reached by garden steps that wind down the hillside. It gives the property a settled, established feel that newer builds rarely match.\n\nHeld on a Chanote-titled plot of roughly 1,666 m² and completed in 2013, the villa sits within easy reach of Bophut’s beach, the restaurants of Fisherman’s Village and the island’s ring road. It suits a buyer after a turnkey hillside home or a proven holiday rental in one of Samui’s most convenient sea-view enclaves.",
